  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne Knight is glad of the encouraging letters to Elizabeth Pease from Lucretia Mott and others. She comments on the conduct of the &quot;orthodox party.&quot; She quotes indirectly a &quot;fulsome address of one of their conclaves, pro-slavery essence! Abolitionists had hurt the cause very much retarded it for years &amp; they could not associate with them!&quot; Anne Knight touches on the woman question and uses a biblical argument in support of a woman&apos;s rights and duties.</subfield>
